    "summary": "CP00-853 is a descriptor-only RP28 Marketplace closeout pack (40 units, risk B, RP28.P02.M07.S13-RP28.P02.M09.S08) covering the Test/Golden-Case tail, Hermes Evidence Packet, and Claude Review Packet head. Read-only inspection of the nine active implementation refs confirms the production-readiness claim is accurately scoped: the manifest declares production_ready=false / runtime_ready=false / in_progress and only descriptor-level evidence is asserted. The marketplace source (registry.js, validators.js, model.js, states.js, index.js), contract JSON, validation script, and tests are internally consistent and fail-closed. The CP853 binding (registry.js:190-205) and requirements (registry.js:674-714) match the planned 40-unit distribution exactly (impl 16 / test 8 / ui 4 / security_audit 4 / failure_recovery 4 / contract 2 / claude_review 2; micro-titles Test-And-Golden-Case 10 / Hermes 22 / Claude-Review 8), and the manifest's 40 included_units sum identically. validateMarketplaceCp853EvidenceReviewPacketDescriptor (validators.js:1063-1131) enforces per-row descriptor_only + runtime_execution=false and rejects connector secrets, OAuth tokens, prompt/completion payloads, real client data, permission-decision detail, audit bodies, runtime opening, and product-state writes; MARKETPLACE_NO_WRITE_ATTESTATION is mirrored in source and contract projection. Authority boundaries hold: Claude is read-only and explicitly not final approver (claude_is_final_approval=false, read_only=true), human approval is required for runtime opening (deferred to next pack CP00-854 via runtime_opening_pack_id), Hermes emits no runtime receipt (emits_runtime_receipt=false), and local validation does not claim enterprise trust. Review hardening is correctly applied: the primary review-receipt.json and three prior attempts are infrastructure failures (API 500 / auth-CLI errors) all quarantined as invalid_review with valid_review_receipts empty; no malformed or tool-shaped output is laundered as valid. The changed-file-scope correctly isolates the nine active refs and preserves unrelated dirty files (progress-control-room, workbook, docx) as out-of-scope. No P0/P1 defects found. Remaining items are non-blocking and harness-enforced: the full 10-command validation suite runs post-review by design (only rp28:marketplace:validate and the marketplace model tests have run, both exit 0), exactly one valid hardened review receipt must be persisted, and construction-inspection.json minorly under-reports the invalid attempts. blocks_goal_closeout=false because the pack explicitly closes runtime/enterprise-trust/final-approval rather than claiming them.",
